{
  "texts": [
    "So while there are applications where greedy policies do much more poorly than a true stochastic control policy, it seems that multi-period trading is not one of them.",
    "Here we directly address the question of sensitivity of Markowitz portfolio construction to the input data µ and Σ.",
    "As mentioned above, the basic methods are indeed sensitive to these parameters.",
    "But this sensitivity can be mitigated and tamed using techniques that are widely used in other applications and fields, robust optimization and regularization.",
    "Robust optimization."
  ]
}